# Troubleshooting

## Session Manager Plugin Not Found

```powershell
session-manager-plugin --version
```

Verify the plugin is installed and included in the PATH.

---

## AWS SSO Login Fails

```powershell
aws sso login --profile np-vega-dev
```

Verify:

- Start URL
- Region
- Account ID
- Role Name

---

## SSH Connection Hangs

Test Session Manager directly:

```powershell
aws ssm start-session --profile np-vega-dev --target <instance-id>
```

If this fails, SSH will also fail.

---

## Permission Denied (Public Key)

Verify:

- Correct PEM file
- Correct EC2 username (`ec2-user`, `dev-user`, etc.)
- Instance was launched using that key pair

---

## VS Code Cannot Connect

Verify:

- `remote.SSH.configFile`
- `remote.SSH.path`
- `remote.SSH.useLocalServer = false`
- Session Manager Plugin is installed
- `AWS_CA_BUNDLE` is configured if required

